news.title: New home prices in China fall again in December 2025; annual decline steepest in five months
news.para: China's real estate sector is still navigating rocky waters, with new home prices dipping once more in December, following a similar trend from November. This ongoing decline hints at a potential protracted slump unless the government steps in with more robust measures.

news.title: Oberoi Realty's net profit grows marginally to ₹622.64 crore in Q3 FY26
news.para: Oberoi Realty has revealed its financial outcomes for the quarter ending December 31, 2025. The company experienced a modest rise in net consolidated profit, along with a growth in total income when compared to the prior year's figures.

news.title: Stable liquidity, office demand keep real estate sentiment firm in Q4 2025
news.para: Indian real estate sentiment stabilized in late 2025. Both current and future outlooks remain positive. Steady economic conditions, lower inflation, and stable funding support the market. Office leasing remains strong, driven by Global Capability Centres. Residential markets show clearer signs of stability. The sector enters 2026 on a steadier footing.

news.title: Aurum PropTech posts net profit of ₹2.71 crore in Q3 FY26
news.para: Aurum PropTech achieved a net profit of ₹2.71 crore in the quarter ending December 31, 2025. This marks a strong recovery from a loss in the same period last year. The company's total income grew by 77.35 percent.

news.title: GCCs account for 45% of office absorption in 2025: Report
news.para: In 2025, Global Capability Centres significantly transformed India's office landscape, driving 45% of all leasing activity. This surge led to a staggering 78.2 million square feet in total office absorption. Alongside this boom, new office supply hit unprecedented levels, with vacancy rates dropping notably across major cities.

news.title: ASK Property Fund invests ₹210 crore in Gami Group's projects in Navi Mumbai
news.para: ASK Property Fund has made a significant leap into the Navi Mumbai real estate scene with a ₹210 crore investment in Gami Group projects, specifically in the thriving locales of CBD Belapur and Ghansoli.

news.title: In Gurugram, buyers protest delay in handover of flats, call for government intervention
news.para: Homebuyers in Gurugram are urging authorities to intervene as construction of the Aashiyara project in Sector 37C remains significantly delayed. Despite full payments made in 2018, buyers are still awaiting possession years later, facing financial strain from servicing loans and paying rent. The project's completion timeline has repeatedly shifted, with work reportedly stalled for the past year.

news.title: Hidco to e-auction two commercial plots in New Town, Kolkata
news.para: Hidco will e-auction two large commercial plots in New Town's central business district next month. One plot spans 10 acres, and the other is 3.9 acres. Both will be sold on a freehold basis. Bids are now open for eligible corporate bodies. Construction must commence within one year of possession. This presents a significant opportunity for business expansion.

news.title: Illegal colonies built on 8.5 acres razed in Gurugram
news.para: The Department of Town and Country Planning (DTCP) in Gurugram has demolished unauthorized colonies spanning 8.5 acres as part of a crackdown on illegal real estate.  This ongoing drive, supported by police, targeted areas in Pataudi and Farukhnagar, removing structures and internal roads to curb unplanned urbanisation and the sale of illegal plots.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body pulled up for delay in giving villages’ list under PMAY-U 2.0
news.para: The Bhubaneswar Development Authority (BDA) faces a stern reminder from the housing and urban development department for failing to submit a crucial list of revenue villages for the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana–Urban 2.0. This delay is jeopardizing the city's eligibility for new housing sanctions, impacting thousands of families.

news.title: Over 62 lakh families benefitted under PMAY-Urban in nine years: Uttar Pradesh CM
news.para: Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath announced that over 62 lakh families have received housing benefits, with an additional 2.09 lakh beneficiaries receiving the first installment of the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Urban) 2.0. This historic step fulfills the dream of permanent housing for many, fostering self-reliance and progress in the state.

news.title: FIR against two builders after techie drowns in Noida pit; junior engineer sacked
news.para: Tragedy struck in Noida's Sector 150 as a software engineer drowned after his car plunged into an unsecured water pit. An FIR has been filed against the builders of MZ Wishtown Planners and Lotus Greens Construction for negligence. The lack of proper fencing and visibility turned the plot into a fatal trap, leading to the young engineer's untimely death.

news.title: Runwal Enterprises secures ₹5,000-crore cluster redevelopment in Marine Lines, Bandra
news.para: Both projects will be taken up under the cluster redevelopment framework under Regulation 33(9) of the Development Control and Promotion Regulations (DCPR), which the state government has been actively promoting to accelerate large-scale urban renewal and infrastructure development.

news.title: Over 70 realty projects didn’t get registration certificates within deadline: RTI reply
news.para: Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority (ORERA) is facing criticism for significant delays in issuing project registration certificates, exceeding the mandated 30-day limit. This is causing financial strain for developers and potential buyers. While ORERA cites incomplete documentation, developers point to internal system weaknesses. New directives aim to expedite the process, but concerns remain about stakeholder representation.

news.title: Amaravati: CRDA plans single layout for returnable plots in LPS second phase
news.para: The Capital Region Development Authority is planning a unified layout for returnable plots in the second phase of land pooling. This move aims to consolidate government-acquired lands for major projects like an international airport and sports complex. Officials believe a single layout will expedite development and infrastructure provision, benefiting farmers and facilitating large-scale allocations.

news.title: NGT issues notices over illegal construction in Rohini green belt
news.para: The National Green Tribunal has issued notices to Delhi pollution control authorities and the DDA regarding illegal construction in Rohini's Sector 16 green belt. The tribunal ordered respondents to take preventive and punitive action within one month, ensuring compliance with the 2021 Master Plan and the Environment Protection Act.

news.title: Lodha Developers net debt up ₹800 crore in Q3 FY26 to ₹6,170 crore due to land purchases
news.para: Lodha Developers saw its net debt climb 15 percent to Rs 6,170 crore. This increase stems from aggressive land acquisitions across Mumbai Metropolitan Region, Delhi-NCR, and Bengaluru. The company is developing new housing projects with a total revenue potential of Rs 33,800 crore.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM orders strict action against irregularities in land lease allocations
news.para: Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath has ordered strict action against irregularities in land lease allocations, emphasizing that no allotment made for monetary gain will be tolerated. During a Janata Darshan, he also directed officials to investigate allegations of land lease discrepancies for the poor and ensure swift justice for citizens.

news.title: NGT seeks responses on ‘illegal construction, environmental violations’ in Haridwar housing project
news.para: The National Green Tribunal has ordered the Uttarakhand Pollution Control Board and Haridwar-Roorkee Development Authority to submit responses. This follows allegations of illegal construction and environmental breaches at the Mantra Happy Homes Group housing project. A resident filed a petition claiming the project's sanctioned plan was revised. The tribunal will hear the case on April 7.

news.title: Telangana to issue TDRs for acquiring land parcels near water bodies
news.para: To boost the use of transferable development rights (TDRs), Hyderabad's municipal administration now mandates that high-rise buildings exceeding 10 floors must incorporate 10% of their built-up area using TDRs.
